name: fried eggs
notes: |
  Temps are Breville Control Freak pan-surface settings.
  Best fried in leftover bacon fat (see meat/bacon); otherwise butter or a neutral oil.
  Seasoned (cast iron / carbon steel) or non-stick are the most forgiving.
  On stainless: bring the pan fully up to temp first, add plenty of fat, and don't move the egg
  until the white has set — otherwise it grabs the surface and tears.
  Egg white sets ~63°C and the yolk thickens ~65-70°C, so keep it gentle to hold a runny yolk.
ingredients:
  - item: eggs
  - item: bacon fat
    note: or butter / neutral oil
  - item: salt & pepper
components:
  - name: soft / sunny side up
    steps:
      - set pan to 130-140°C
      - add fat, then crack in the eggs
      - cook gently until the whites set but the yolk stays runny — starting estimate ~3-4 mins uncovered (refine to taste)
      - to set the tops, baste with the hot fat or cover with a lid — whites set faster, so check ~2.5-3 mins
      - season and serve
  - name: crispy edges
    steps:
      - set pan to 180-190°C with a little extra fat
      - crack in the eggs — the edges will bubble up and crisp
      - baste the yolks or cover briefly to set the tops; season
